Here is the usage documentation for the Popover component:

## Summary

The `<Popover>` component is a versatile floating surface that hosts a focused interaction next to a source element. It can be used to display various types of content, such as details, edit forms, or tool menus, and it provides a range of customization options for the visual appearance and behavior of the popover.

## Import

```javascript
import Popover from '../popover-0eb44ed4-450d-4212-9cec-2749125c8b98/46f065-popover/popover';
```

## Usage as a Field

To use the Popover component as a field within a consuming card or field, you can include it in the template and pass the necessary arguments:

```hbs
<Popover
  @anchor=".my-anchor-element"
  @open={{this.isPopoverOpen}}
  @kind="details"
  @onDismiss={{this.handlePopoverDismiss}}
  @onEscalate={{this.handlePopoverEscalate}}
  @focusToken={{this.popoverFocusToken}}
>
  <div>
    Popover content goes here
  </div>
</Popover>
```

## Template Usage

You can also invoke the Popover component directly in a template within a consuming card or field:

```hbs
<button
  type="button"
  class="my-anchor-element"
  {{on "click" (toggle "isPopoverOpen" this)}}
>
  Open Popover
</button>

{{#if this.isPopoverOpen}}
  <Popover
    @anchor=".my-anchor-element"
    @open={{this.isPopoverOpen}}
    @kind="details"
    @onDismiss={{this.handlePopoverDismiss}}
    @onEscalateTo={{this.handlePopoverEscalate}}
    @focusToken={{this.popoverFocusToken}}
  >
    <div>
      Popover content goes here
    </div>
  </Popover>
{{/if}}
```

In this example, the Popover is displayed when the button is clicked, and it is dismissed when the user clicks outside the popover or presses the Escape key.
